## Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how Level-Up Developer collects, uses, and protects your information through the IA‑Parking app.

IA‑Parking is provided by Level-Up Developer as a **free app**, and is intended for use as-is.

By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. The personal information we collect is used for improving and providing the service. We do not share your information with anyone except as described here.

Unless otherwise stated, the terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as those in our Terms and Conditions, available on our website.

---

## Information We Collect

### 1. Personal Information
We may ask you to provide personal information such as:
- Full name  
- Email address  
- Gender  
- Location  
- Profile photo(s)

This information is retained and used as described in this policy.

### 2. Vehicle Information
We collect data related to your vehicle, including:
- Vehicle registration number  
- Vehicle type  
- Owner details  
- Parking zone and location data  

### 3. Document Images
We may collect images of identity or verification documents such as:
- National ID  
- Driver’s license  
- Other required documents

### 4. Chat Data
We store chat messages and any media (images, videos, files) shared through the in-app messaging feature for support and communication purposes.

### 5. Location Information
Some features require access to your mobile device's location, used only as needed for:
- Detecting nearby parking zones  
- Logging your parked location  

### 6. Device Information
We collect technical data from your device to improve the service and detect fraud, including:
- Device ID  
- Operating system  
- App version  
- Hardware details  

This information does **not** personally identify you.

### 7. Cookies
Cookies are small data files used to uniquely identify you anonymously.  
While the app itself does not use cookies directly, some third-party code and libraries may use them to improve functionality.

You can choose to accept or refuse cookies. Refusing cookies may limit some features of the app.

---

## How We Use the Collected Data

The collected information is used for purposes such as:
- Vehicle parking management  
- User authentication and account management  
- Location-based parking services  
- Document verification  
- Customer support and in-app communication  
- Fraud prevention and service security  
- Service analytics and improvement  

---

## Third-Party Services

We use the following third-party services that may collect information used to identify you:

- **Firebase (Google)** – For push notifications, analytics, and user authentication  
- **Geolocation services** – For detecting and managing parking zones  
- **Image hosting services** – For storing user and document images  

These providers have access to your information only to perform tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to use or disclose it for any other purpose.

---

## Security

We value your trust in providing your personal information. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect it, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.

---

## Children’s Privacy

Our service does not address users under the age of 13.  
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal data, we will delete it immediately.

If you are a parent or guardian and you become aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we can take appropriate action.

---

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. You are advised to review this page periodically for any changes.

We will notify you of any changes by posting the updated policy on this page. Changes take effect immediately after being posted.

